      "span_text": "The optical path length was varied using a frequency-domain optical delay line (FD-ODL) [CITATION_1] in the reference arm to achieve an Ascan rate of 500 Hz, with a measured axial resolution of ∼8 μm in air and system sensitivity of 104 dB. Lateral scanning in one dimension (x) was achieved by a galvanometer mirror and objective lens setup with an NA of 0.07 and measured lateral resolution of ∼11 μm at the beam waist (1/e 2 intensity of beam diameter).",
